SIMPLE: impeccable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impeccable
<hw>Im*pec"ca*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>impeccabilis</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>peccare</ets>
to err, to sin: cf. F. <ets>impeccable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not liable to
sin; exempt from the possibility of doing wrong.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>One who is impeccable; esp., one of a sect of
Gnostic heretics who asserted their sinlessness.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God is infallible, <qex>impeccable</qex>, and absolutely
perfect.</q> <rj><qau>P. Skelton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impeccancy</ent>⟦br⟧
